    "description": {
      "value": "<em>You are skilled at concealing your use of magic items with guile and deft tricks.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Stealthy.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>When triggering a wand, staff or any other magic item, you can attempt a Stealth check (opposed by observers' Perception checks) to conceal the trigger from onlookers. If the magic item produces an obvious effect (such as a summoned creature or visible spell effect), you take a -4 penalty on the Stealth check, and even if your check is successful, observers still see the spell effect (though they fail to notice you are responsible for it).",
